annotationA: 40S ribosomal protein SA; Required for the assembly and/or stability of the 40S ribosomal subunit. Required for the processing of the 20S rRNA- precursor to mature 18S rRNA in a late step of the maturation of 40S ribosomal subunits. Required during oogenesis and imaginal development
annotationB: Pixie, isoform A; Pixie encodes ABCE1, which is an ATPase that functions as a translation recycling factor. It is required  for the assembly of complexes involved in translation initiation, and plays a role in the regulation of cellular and organismal growth
